A cliff. What. Though at the #main-basin, the sky lift up to here says that it's the "Advanced Slope", it's... just a cliff. There are lights and flags that show the path down, but honestly, the path is so sharply inclined that it deserves the name of "Cliff" instead. It's much shorter than the other paths, only about 100 meters or so, but going down it would surely kill someone. The path is littered with sharp rocks, designed to stab anyone who crashed into them. Unforgiving turns and loops are along the path, complete with a drop directly down at the very end. At the top of the cliff itself (before you go down) is a little hut. You won't be able to get in. The hut is made of wooden boards, and doesn't look very well kept. The door is locked shut, but you might be able to get in one day. (edited)
